1
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,919
<font color="#FFFFFF">You've seen better days, my lord.</font>

2
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:13,210
<font color="#FFFFFF">Another visit?</font>

3
00:02:14,919 --> 00:02:16,960
<font color="#FFFFFF">It seems you're my last friend.</font>

4
00:02:17,090 --> 00:02:19,930
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, no, many still love you.</font>

5
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:25,310
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sansa came to court this morning
to plead for your life.</font>

6
00:02:26,719 --> 00:02:29,229
<font color="#FFFFFF">On her knees begging for me. Hm!</font>

7
00:02:29,349 --> 00:02:31,479
<font color="#FFFFFF">Did you laugh with the others?</font>

8
00:02:31,599 --> 00:02:35,150
<font color="#FFFFFF">You do me wrong, my lord.
Your blood is the last thing I want.</font>

9
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,150
<font color="#FFFFFF">I don't know what you want.</font>

10
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:38,900
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've given up trying to guess.</font>

11
00:02:42,449 --> 00:02:44,530
<font color="#FFFFFF">When I was still a boy -</font>

12
00:02:45,409 --> 00:02:48,449
<font color="#FFFFFF">before they cut my balls off with a hot knife -</font>

13
00:02:48,579 --> 00:02:52,000
<font color="#FFFFFF">I traveled with a group of actors
through the free cities.</font>

14
00:02:53,629 --> 00:02:56,629
<font color="#FFFFFF">They taught me that
each man has a role to play.</font>

15
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:59,509
<font color="#FFFFFF">The same is true at court.</font>

16
00:02:59,629 --> 00:03:01,879
<font color="#FFFFFF">I am the master of whisperers.</font>

17
00:03:02,009 --> 00:03:06,389
<font color="#FFFFFF">My role is to be sly, obsequious
and without scruples.</font>

18
00:03:06,509 --> 00:03:08,469
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm a good actor, my lord.</font>

19
00:03:08,599 --> 00:03:11,849
<font color="#FFFFFF">Huh. Can you free me from this pit?</font>

20
00:03:11,979 --> 00:03:13,979
<font color="#FFFFFF">I could.</font>

21
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:15,439
<font color="#FFFFFF">But will l?</font>

22
00:03:16,110 --> 00:03:17,900
<font color="#FFFFFF">No.</font>

23
00:03:18,030 --> 00:03:19,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">As I said, I'm no hero.</font>

24
00:03:20,110 --> 00:03:21,860
<font color="#FFFFFF">What do you want? Tell me.</font>

25
00:03:21,990 --> 00:03:24,819
<font color="#FFFFFF">No riddles, no stories...
Tell me, what do you want?</font>

26
00:03:26,909 --> 00:03:28,539
<font color="#FFFFFF">Peace.</font>

27
00:03:28,659 --> 00:03:34,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">Did you know that your son is marching south
with an army of northmen? Loyal lad.</font>

28
00:03:34,829 --> 00:03:37,170
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fighting for his father's freedom.</font>

29
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:39,460
<font color="#FFFFFF">Robb?</font>

30
00:03:39,590 --> 00:03:41,379
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's just a boy.</font>

31
00:03:41,509 --> 00:03:43,719
<font color="#FFFFFF">Boys have been conquerors before.</font>

32
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:50,389
<font color="#FFFFFF">But the man giving Cersei sleepless nights
is the king's... the late king's brother.</font>

33
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:53,270
<font color="#FFFFFF">Lord Stannis has the best claim to the throne.</font>

34
00:03:53,389 --> 00:03:56,560
<font color="#FFFFFF">He is a proven battle commander
and he is utterly without mercy.</font>

35
00:03:56,689 --> 00:04:01,069
<font color="#FFFFFF">Stannis Baratheon is Robert's true heir.
The throne is his by rights.</font>

36
00:04:02,860 --> 00:04:07,909
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sansa pleaded so sweetly for your life.
It would be a shame to throw it away.</font>

37
00:04:09,539 --> 00:04:11,539
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cersei is no fool.</font>

38
00:04:11,659 --> 00:04:14,960
<font color="#FFFFFF">She knows a tame wolf
is more use to her than a dead one.</font>

39
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:18,629
<font color="#FFFFFF">You want me to serve the woman who
murdered my king, who butchered my men,</font>

40
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:20,339
<font color="#FFFFFF">who crippled my son?</font>

41
00:04:20,459 --> 00:04:22,379
<font color="#FFFFFF">I want you to serve the realm!</font>

42
00:04:22,509 --> 00:04:25,220
<font color="#FFFFFF">Tell the queen you will confess
your vile treason,</font>

43
00:04:25,339 --> 00:04:27,339
<font color="#FFFFFF">tell your son to lay down his sword</font>

44
00:04:27,470 --> 00:04:30,680
<font color="#FFFFFF">and proclaim Joffrey as the true heir.</font>

45
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:35,730
<font color="#FFFFFF">Cersei knows you as a man of honor.</font>

46
00:04:36,730 --> 00:04:40,610
<font color="#FFFFFF">if you give her the peace she needs,
and promise to carry her secret to your grave,</font>

47
00:04:40,730 --> 00:04:43,319
<font color="#FFFFFF">I believe she will allow you
to take the black</font>

48
00:04:43,439 --> 00:04:46,949
<font color="#FFFFFF">and live out your days on the Wall
with your brother and your bastard son.</font>

49
00:04:48,529 --> 00:04:50,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">You think my life
is some precious thing to me?</font>

50
00:04:52,579 --> 00:04:55,829
<font color="#FFFFFF">That I would trade my honor
for a few more years of...</font>

51
00:04:55,959 --> 00:04:57,579
<font color="#FFFFFF">Of what?</font>

52
00:05:02,509 --> 00:05:04,550
<font color="#FFFFFF">You grew up with actors.</font>

53
00:05:06,129 --> 00:05:09,009
<font color="#FFFFFF">You learned their craft and you learnt it well.</font>

54
00:05:10,180 --> 00:05:12,470
<font color="#FFFFFF">But I grew up with soldiers.</font>

55
00:05:14,980 --> 00:05:16,939
<font color="#FFFFFF">I learned how to die a long time ago.</font>

56
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:21,769
<font color="#FFFFFF">Pity.</font>

57
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:24,740
<font color="#FFFFFF">Such a pity.</font>

58
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:33,949
<font color="#FFFFFF">What of your daughter's life, my lord?</font>

59
00:05:34,079 --> 00:05:36,500
<font color="#FFFFFF">Is that a precious thing to you?</font>

60
00:06:18,079 --> 00:06:20,870
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's a birthday message
to his grand-niece Walda.</font>

61
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,709
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Or so Walder Frey would have you think.
- Keep shooting them down.</font>

62
00:06:24,839 --> 00:06:27,879
<font color="#FFFFFF">We can't risk Lord Walder sending
word of your movements to the Lannisters.</font>

63
00:06:28,009 --> 00:06:30,970
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's Grandfather's bannerman.
We can't expect his support?</font>

64
00:06:31,089 --> 00:06:34,889
<font color="#FFFFFF">Expect nothing of Walder Frey
and you'll never be surprised.</font>

65
00:06:35,009 --> 00:06:36,139
<font color="#FFFFFF">Look.</font>

66
00:06:38,350 --> 00:06:40,100
<font color="#FFFFFF">Father rots in a dungeon.</font>

67
00:06:40,230 --> 00:06:42,310
<font color="#FFFFFF">How long before they take his head?</font>

68
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,439
<font color="#FFFFFF">We need to cross the Trident
and we need to do it now.</font>

69
00:06:45,569 --> 00:06:48,029
<font color="#FFFFFF">Just march up to his gates
and tell him you're crossing.</font>

70
00:06:48,149 --> 00:06:51,069
<font color="#FFFFFF">We've got five times his numbers.
You can take the Twins if you have to.</font>

71
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:54,569
<font color="#FFFFFF">Not in time.
Tywin Lannister marches north as we speak.</font>

72
00:06:54,699 --> 00:06:57,370
<font color="#FFFFFF">The Freys have
held the crossing for 600 years,</font>

73
00:06:57,500 --> 00:07:00,620
<font color="#FFFFFF">and for 600 years
they have never failed to exact their toll.</font>

74
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:03,000
<font color="#FFFFFF">Have my horse saddled and ready.</font>

75
00:07:03,129 --> 00:07:06,209
<font color="#FFFFFF">Enter the Twins alone and he'll sell you
to the Lannisters as he likes.</font>

76
00:07:06,339 --> 00:07:09,129
<font color="#FFFFFF">Or throw you in a dungeon.
Or slit your throat.</font>

77
00:07:11,930 --> 00:07:14,889
<font color="#FFFFFF">My father would do whatever it took
to secure our crossing.</font>

78
00:07:15,009 --> 00:07:17,259
<font color="#FFFFFF">Whatever it took.</font>

79
00:07:17,389 --> 00:07:21,939
<font color="#FFFFFF">if I'm going to lead this army, I can't have
other men doing my bargaining for me.</font>

80
00:07:22,060 --> 00:07:23,230
<font color="#FFFFFF">I agree.</font>

81
00:07:25,189 --> 00:07:26,439
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I'll go.
- You can't!</font>

82
00:07:26,569 --> 00:07:30,860
<font color="#FFFFFF">I have known Lord Walder since I was a girl.
He would never harm me.</font>

83
00:07:30,990 --> 00:07:33,409
<font color="#FFFFFF">Unless there was a profit in it.</font>

84
00:07:39,540 --> 00:07:41,000
<font color="#FFFFFF">What do you want?</font>

85
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:44,670
<font color="#FFFFFF">It is a great pleasure to see you again
after so many years, my lord.</font>

86
00:07:44,790 --> 00:07:46,500
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, spare me.</font>

87
00:07:46,629 --> 00:07:50,709
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your boy's too proud
to come before me himself.</font>

88
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:52,840
<font color="#FFFFFF">What am I supposed to do with you?</font>

89
00:07:52,970 --> 00:07:55,970
<font color="#FFFFFF">Father, you forget yourself.
Lady Stark is here...</font>

90
00:07:56,100 --> 00:08:02,180
<font color="#FFFFFF">Who asked you? You're not Lord Frey yet,
not until I die. Do I look dead to you?</font>

91
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:06,060
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Father, please...
- I need lessons in courtesy from you, bastard?</font>

92
00:08:06,189 --> 00:08:11,569
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your mother would still be a milkmaid
if I hadn't squirted you into her belly.</font>

93
00:08:15,319 --> 00:08:18,160
<font color="#FFFFFF">All right, you come forward.</font>

94
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:32,299
<font color="#FFFFFF">There.
Now that I've observed the courtesies,</font>

95
00:08:32,419 --> 00:08:35,799
<font color="#FFFFFF">perhaps my sons will do me the honor
of shutting their mouths.</font>

96
00:08:41,269 --> 00:08:43,179
<font color="#FFFFFF">ls there somewhere we can talk?</font>

97
00:08:43,309 --> 00:08:45,309
<font color="#FFFFFF">We're talking right now.</font>

98
00:08:49,399 --> 00:08:50,860
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fine.</font>

99
00:08:50,980 --> 00:08:53,529
<font color="#FFFFFF">Out! All of you!</font>

100
00:09:03,659 --> 00:09:05,289
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Oh!
- You too.</font>

101
00:09:12,669 --> 00:09:14,799
<font color="#FFFFFF">You see that?</font>

102
00:09:14,919 --> 00:09:16,970
<font color="#FFFFFF">Fifteen, she is.</font>

103
00:09:17,090 --> 00:09:18,889
<font color="#FFFFFF">A little flower.</font>

104
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:23,429
<font color="#FFFFFF">And her honey's all mine.</font>

105
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:28,190
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm sure she will give you many sons.</font>

106
00:09:28,899 --> 00:09:31,940
<font color="#FFFFFF">Huh.
Your father didn't come to the wedding.</font>

107
00:09:32,070 --> 00:09:33,980
<font color="#FFFFFF">He is quite ill, my lord.</font>

108
00:09:34,110 --> 00:09:37,240
<font color="#FFFFFF">Huh. Didn't come to the last one, either.</font>

109
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:39,529
<font color="#FFFFFF">Or the one before that.</font>

110
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:43,159
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your family has always pissed on me.</font>

111
00:09:43,289 --> 00:09:46,159
<font color="#FFFFFF">- My lord, l...
- Don't deny it. You know it's true.</font>

112
00:09:46,289 --> 00:09:50,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">The fine Lord Tully would never marry
any of his children to mine.</font>

113
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:53,750
<font color="#FFFFFF">- I'm sure there were reasons...
- I didn't need reasons.</font>

114
00:09:53,879 --> 00:09:58,549
<font color="#FFFFFF">I needed to get rid of sons and daughters.
You see how they pile up?</font>

115
00:10:02,679 --> 00:10:04,100
<font color="#FFFFFF">Why are you here?</font>

116
00:10:06,350 --> 00:10:07,769
<font color="#FFFFFF">To ask you...</font>

117
00:10:07,889 --> 00:10:10,149
<font color="#FFFFFF">to open your gates, my lord...</font>

118
00:10:11,059 --> 00:10:14,769
<font color="#FFFFFF">so my son and his bannermen
may cross the Trident and be on their way.</font>

119
00:10:14,899 --> 00:10:17,940
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Why should I let him?
- if you could climb your own battlements,</font>

120
00:10:18,070 --> 00:10:21,570
<font color="#FFFFFF">you would see that he has
20,000 men outside your walls.</font>

121
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:25,080
<font color="#FFFFFF">They'll be 20,000 corpses
when Tywin Lannister gets here.</font>

122
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,539
<font color="#FFFFFF">Don't try and frighten me, Lady Stark.</font>

123
00:10:27,659 --> 00:10:30,039
<font color="#FFFFFF">Your husband's in a cell
beneath the Red Keep</font>

124
00:10:30,169 --> 00:10:33,000
<font color="#FFFFFF">and your son's got no fur
to keep his balls warm.</font>

125
00:10:33,129 --> 00:10:35,460
<font color="#FFFFFF">You swore an oath to my father.</font>

126
00:10:35,590 --> 00:10:38,629
<font color="#FFFFFF">Oh, yes, I said some words.</font>

127
00:10:38,759 --> 00:10:41,929
<font color="#FFFFFF">And I swore oaths to the crown too,
if I remember right.</font>

128
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:44,299
<font color="#FFFFFF">Joffrey's king now,</font>

129
00:10:44,429 --> 00:10:49,059
<font color="#FFFFFF">which makes your boy and his corpses-to-be
nothing but rebels, it seems to me.</font>

130
00:10:50,899 --> 00:10:54,980
<font color="#FFFFFF">if I had the sense the gods gave a fish,
I'd hand you both over to the Lannisters.</font>

131
00:10:55,110 --> 00:10:59,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Why don't you?
- Stark, Tully, Lannister, Baratheon.</font>

132
00:11:01,450 --> 00:11:06,200
<font color="#FFFFFF">Give me one good reason why I should
waste a single thought on any of you?</font>

133
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:08,700
<font color="#FFFFFF">And... engage!</font>

134
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:14,000
<font color="#FFFFFF">When does Aemon think
you'll be able to use that hand?</font>

135
00:11:14,129 --> 00:11:16,289
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Soon, he says.
- Good.</font>

136
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:20,169
<font color="#FFFFFF">You'll be ready for this, then.</font>

137
00:11:20,299 --> 00:11:24,970
<font color="#FFFFFF">I thought a wolf was more
appropriate for you than a bear...</font>

138
00:11:26,350 --> 00:11:29,559
<font color="#FFFFFF">so I had a new pommel made.
It's called Longclaw.</font>

139
00:11:30,769 --> 00:11:33,309
<font color="#FFFFFF">Works as well for a wolf as a bear, I think.</font>

140
00:11:44,529 --> 00:11:45,990
<font color="#FFFFFF">This is Valyrian steel.</font>

141
00:11:47,789 --> 00:11:51,710
<font color="#FFFFFF">It was my father's sword,
his father before him.</font>

142
00:11:51,830 --> 00:11:55,210
<font color="#FFFFFF">The Mormonts have carried it
for five centuries.</font>

143
00:11:55,330 --> 00:11:57,340
<font color="#FFFFFF">It was meant for my son Jorah.</font>

144
00:11:58,169 --> 00:12:03,169
<font color="#FFFFFF">He brought dishonor to our House,
but he had the grace to leave the sword</font>

145
00:12:03,299 --> 00:12:05,549
<font color="#FFFFFF">before he fled from Westeros.</font>

146
00:12:06,429 --> 00:12:09,720
<font color="#FFFFFF">- My lord, you honor me, but I can't...
- Oh, you can.</font>

147
00:12:09,850 --> 00:12:11,559
<font color="#FFFFFF">And you will.</font>

148
00:12:11,679 --> 00:12:15,559
<font color="#FFFFFF">I wouldn't be standing here
if it wasn't for you and your beast.</font>

149
00:12:15,690 --> 00:12:18,360
<font color="#FFFFFF">A bloody dead man tried to kill me.</font>

150
00:12:20,779 --> 00:12:24,070
<font color="#FFFFFF">So you'll take it.
I'll hear no more about it.</font>

151
00:12:24,860 --> 00:12:26,909
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Is that understood?
- Yes, my lord.</font>

152
00:12:27,029 --> 00:12:28,620
<font color="#FFFFFF">Right.</font>

153
00:12:28,740 --> 00:12:34,620
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now, don't think this means I approve
of this nonsense with you and Alliser Thorne.</font>

154
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:38,210
<font color="#FFFFFF">That's a man's sword.
It'll take a man to wield it.</font>

155
00:12:39,750 --> 00:12:41,590
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'll apologize to Ser Alliser tonight.</font>

156
00:12:41,710 --> 00:12:45,090
<font color="#FFFFFF">No, you won't.
I sent him to King's Landing yesterday.</font>

157
00:12:45,220 --> 00:12:49,220
<font color="#FFFFFF">The hand that your wolf tore off
that thing's wrist...</font>

158
00:12:49,350 --> 00:12:52,639
<font color="#FFFFFF">I've, uh, ordered Thorne
to lay it at the feet of this...</font>

159
00:12:52,769 --> 00:12:54,600
<font color="#FFFFFF">boy king.</font>

160
00:12:54,730 --> 00:12:57,559
<font color="#FFFFFF">That should get young Joffrey's attention.</font>

161
00:12:58,559 --> 00:13:03,779
<font color="#FFFFFF">And it, uh, puts a thousand leagues
between you and Thorne.</font>

162
00:13:03,899 --> 00:13:06,450
<font color="#FFFFFF">Now go and put your sword somewhere safe...</font>

163
00:13:06,570 --> 00:13:08,950
<font color="#FFFFFF">and bring me my supper.</font>

164
00:13:09,070 --> 00:13:10,620
<font color="#FFFFFF">Yes, my lord.</font>

165
00:13:22,210 --> 00:13:24,509
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Well done.
- Well done.</font>

166
00:13:26,549 --> 00:13:28,259
<font color="#FFFFFF">You earned that, Snow.</font>

167
00:13:32,350 --> 00:13:34,269
<font color="#FFFFFF">Well done.</font>

168
00:13:38,769 --> 00:13:40,190
<font color="#FFFFFF">Go on, let's have a look.</font>

169
00:13:40,309 --> 00:13:42,610
<font color="#FFFFFF">- At what?
- The sword! Show us the sword.</font>

170
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:45,649
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sword! Sword! Sword! Sword!</font>

171
00:13:45,779 --> 00:13:49,029
<font color="#FFFFFF">Sword! Sword! Sword! Sword! Sword!</font>

172
00:13:54,289 --> 00:13:55,950
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Let's have a look.
- Piss off.</font>

173
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:01,960
<font color="#FFFFFF">Come on,
I want to have a look at it in the light.</font>

174
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,840
<font color="#FFFFFF">Give it here!</font>

175
00:14:06,970 --> 00:14:08,840
<font color="#FFFFFF">What is it?</font>

176
00:14:08,970 --> 00:14:10,970
<font color="#FFFFFF">- l...
- Look at its eyes.</font>

177
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:12,600
<font color="#FFFFFF">- Give it.
- I can't.</font>

178
00:14:13,559 --> 00:14:15,179
<font color="#FFFFFF">You can't what?</font>

179
00:14:15,309 --> 00:14:16,470
<font color="#FFFFFF">l...</font>

180
00:14:18,230 --> 00:14:20,769
<font color="#FFFFFF">I'm really not supposed to say.</font>

181
00:14:20,899 --> 00:14:23,519
<font color="#FFFFFF">And yet you really want to say.</font>

182
00:14:23,649 --> 00:14:25,610
<font color="#FFFFFF">You want to say that...?</font>

183
00:14:28,990 --> 00:14:31,700
<font color="#FFFFFF">There was a raven.</font>

184
00:14:31,820 --> 00:14:33,700
<font color="#FFFFFF">I read the message to Maester Aemon.</font>

185
00:14:36,159 --> 00:14:38,000
<font color="#FFFFFF">It's your brother Robb.</font>

186
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,870
<font color="#FFFFFF">What?</font>

187
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,500
<font color="#FFFFFF">What about him?</font>

188
00:14:42,919 --> 00:14:44,460
<font color="#FFFFFF">He's heading south.</font>

189
00:14:44,590 --> 00:14:46,379
<font color="#FFFFFF">To war.</font>

190
00:14:48,590 --> 00:14:52,429
<font color="#FFFFFF">All his bannermen have rallied to his side.
